# Hoist mobile's node_modules to a flat layout (npm/yarn-style).
#
# Why: react-native-reanimated 4.x (transitive peer of expo-router) runs a
# Node `require.resolve('react-native')` inside its android/build.gradle at
# evaluation time. Under pnpm's default symlink layout the nested
# .pnpm/<hash>/node_modules paths can't see the project's top-level
# react-native, so the Gradle exec fails with
#   `Process 'command 'node'' finished with non-zero exit value 1`
# and the EAS build crashes before assembleDebug.
#
# `node-linker=hoisted` makes pnpm install a flat tree at
# packages/mobile/node_modules — same shape Gradle expects from npm/yarn —
# while leaving the rest of the monorepo (api, web, shared) on pnpm's
# default symlinked layout.
#
# Reference: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/monorepos/ ("Using pnpm" section).
node-linker=hoisted
